  "title" : "Find the substring between two &quot;/&quot;",
  "body" : "<p>For this program the user is told to input a data in the form of \"mm/dd/yyyy\" and I'm trying to use the <code>indexOf()</code> method with the parameter of \"/\" to break the date string into three substrings. </p>\n\n<p>I tried doing this:</p>\n\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>String monthString = dateString.substring(0,dateString.indexOf(\"/\"));\n    String dayString = \n    dateString.substring(dateString.indexOf(\"/\"),DateString.indexOf(\"/\")+1)\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Thank you.\nEdit. Thank you all for your responses, but my teacher said that i cannot use the split fucntion. He said I can solve this using just indexOf(\"/\") and substring(). I'll need two calls to indexOf(\"/\") and four calls to substring().</p>\n"
}